name: MicroServiceDemo-ServerSideWebApplication
description: This is For Demo Application For Using MicroService

name: bank-microservice
description: This repository demonstrates micro services that can be present inside a banking application.

name: CityHotel-Microservices
description: A simple spring boot microservices application with two independent services: City service which will manage city list and Hotel service which will simply fetch hotels in each city. For this application we will make use of Spring Cloud projects.

name: Quiz-Question-Microservices
description: A microservices-based application for managing quizzes and questions where the quiz service retrieves quizzes by ID, including all associated questions from the question service.

name: SpringBootMicroServices-MongoDB
description: A comprehensive microservices application leveraging the power of Spring Boot, MongoDB, and RESTful APIs. This project showcases a modular architecture that includes multiple microservices, each designed for specific functionalities and seamlessly integrated with Eureka for service discovery.

name: IoT-Microservice-MQTT
description: This is part two of a project for course Internet of Things and Services. It is a microservice application, meaning it is divided into multiple services, each with its own responsibility. It was written in Python and .NET Core, and uses PostgreSQL as the database. The focus here is on microservice communication using a MQTT, specifically Mosquitto.

name: job-portal-spring-boot-microservice
description: A microservices-based job portal application for managing job listings, company profiles, and reviews. Built with Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, and Docker. Features include dynamic service discovery with Eureka, centralized API routing with Spring Gateway, and configuration management with Spring Cloud Config. Includes Zipkin for distributed tracing.
